 The Nigerian Grammy award-winning artist, Damini Ebunoluwa Ogulu popularly known as Burna Boy has set a new record on the global streaming platform, Spotify with 3 billion streams across all credits. According to chart metrics, Burna Boy’s top five-track is, “Last Last”, “Location”, “Ye”, “Own It” and “Be Honest”. His current song “Last Last” reached 6 million streams on Spotify and is also one of the most-streamed songs in Nigeria. The artist has a total of 9,823,658 monthly Spotify listeners and 1.2 billion YouTube views. Read also: Davido’s North American tour concert begins in New York According to mp3bullet.ng, the afro-fusion star has become the first Nigerian Afrobeats artist to sell out the iconic 3Arena in Dublin, Ireland. His forthcoming album “Love Damini”, set to release on the 1st of July, one day before his birthday, has gained interesting numbers on streaming platforms. The album is currently sitting on the number 3 spot on the Apple Music album charts.